<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="1476" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1476">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/214.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Special Agent <persName type="to">Carothers</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-24">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department informed Colonel Borboa, Villista commander San Luis Potosí,
                            threatening confiscation foreign mining property and imposition forced
                            loan upon foreigners, within five days.</p>
                        <p>In calling this particular case to General Villa’s immediate attention
                            request him to issue general instructions to his commanders directing
                            them to respect foreign rights and property. Such an order from General
                            Villa would obviate repeated representations, save trouble and enable
                            foreigners to enjoy with greater security the guarantees which they are
                            entitled to and should have.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>